{
  "local_port": 37622,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I stop Outlook from synchronising folders automatically?",
  "response": "To prevent Outlook from automatically synchronizing specific folders, you can adjust your **Send/Receive** settings or manage folder subscriptions based on the type of email account you're using. Below are detailed steps for both **IMAP** and **Exchange/Office 365** accounts. These instructions are generally applicable to recent versions of Outlook, including Outlook 2016, Outlook 2019, and Microsoft 365.\n\n---\n\n### **For IMAP Accounts: Unsubscribe from Unwanted Folders**\n\nIMAP accounts synchronize all subscribed folders by default. To stop synchronizing specific folders:\n\n1. **Open Outlook.**\n\n2. **Navigate to IMAP Folders:**\n   - **Outlook 2016/2019/Microsoft 365:**\n     - Click on the **Send/Receive** tab.\n     - Select **Send/Receive Groups** > **Define Send/Receive Groups**.\n   - **Alternatively:**\n     - Right-click your IMAP account in the folder pane.\n     - Select **IMAP Folders**.\n\n3. **Manage Subscriptions:**\n   - In the **IMAP Folders** dialog, click **Query** to list all available folders on the server.\n   - Browse through the list and **select the folders** you **do not** want to synchronize.\n   - Click **Unsubscribe**.\n\n4. **Confirm and Close:**\n   - After unsubscribing, click **OK** to save changes.\n   - Outlook will no longer automatically sync the unsubscribed folders.\n\n---\n\n### **For Exchange or Office 365 Accounts: Adjust Send/Receive Settings**\n\nWhile Exchange accounts typically sync all folders, you can customize which folders are included in the synchronization process by modifying the **Send/Receive Group** settings.\n\n1. **Open Outlook.**\n\n2. **Access Send/Receive Groups:**\n   - Click on the **Send/Receive** tab.\n   - Select **Send/Receive Groups** > **Define Send/Receive Groups**.\n\n3. **Select the Appropriate Group:**\n   - Normally, the default group is named **All Accounts**. Select it and click **Edit**.\n\n4. **Customize Folder Synchronization:**\n   - In the left pane, select your **Exchange account**.\n   - You'll see a list of **mail folders**. Uncheck the folders you **do not** want Outlook to synchronize automatically.\n   - Note: Some default folders (like Inbox, Sent Items) might be required and cannot be deselected.\n\n5. **Save Changes:**\n   - Click **OK** to save the configuration.\n   - Then click **Close** in the **Send/Receive Groups** dialog.\n\n---\n\n### **Alternative Method: Disable Cached Exchange Mode**\n\n**Cached Exchange Mode** allows Outlook to keep a local copy of your mailbox. Disabling it can reduce synchronization but will require a constant connection to the Exchange server.\n\n1. **Open Outlook.**\n\n2. **Go to Account Settings:**\n   - Click on **File** > **Account Settings** > **Account Settings**.\n\n3. **Modify Exchange Account:**\n   - Select your **Exchange account** and click **Change**.\n\n4. **Disable Cached Exchange Mode:**\n   - Uncheck the box labeled **Use Cached Exchange Mode**.\n   - Click **Next**, then **Finish**.\n   - **Restart Outlook** for changes to take effect.\n\n**Note:** Disabling Cached Exchange Mode may impact performance and offline access. Use this method only if necessary.\n\n---\n\n### **Prevent All Automatic Synchronization**\n\nIf you prefer to control synchronization manually, you can disable automatic send/receive intervals:\n\n1. **Open Outlook.**\n\n2. **Access Send/Receive Groups:**\n   - Click on the **Send/Receive** tab.\n   - Select **Send/Receive Groups** > **Define Send/Receive Groups**.\n\n3. **Edit Group Settings:**\n   - Select **All Accounts** (or the relevant group) and click **Edit**.\n\n4. **Disable Automatic Sync:**\n   - Uncheck **Schedule an automatic send/receive every X minutes**.\n   - Click **OK**, then **Close**.\n\n**Result:** Outlook will no longer automatically synchronize. You'll need to manually initiate synchronization by clicking **Send/Receive All Folders**.\n\n---\n\n### **Summary**\n\n- **IMAP Accounts:** Unsubscribe from folders you don't want to sync via **IMAP Folders** settings.\n- **Exchange/Office 365 Accounts:** Customize folder synchronization through **Send/Receive Groups**.\n- **Cached Exchange Mode:** Consider disabling it to reduce synchronization but be aware of the implications.\n- **Manual Control:** Disable automatic send/receive to have full control over when synchronization happens.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively manage which folders Outlook synchronizes automatically, helping you save bandwidth, improve performance, or maintain focus on relevant emails.\n\n---\n\n**If you encounter any issues or the options aren't available as described, please ensure your Outlook application is up to date or consult your IT administrator, especially in a corporate environment.**",
